h to turn the damn heads in!!<br><br>Ok, venting over. :P But seriously, can someone give me an idea of just how much longer this mind-numbing killing must continue till I can at least make some headway with Riff and Zek? If possible, I would prefer holding on to the heads for Bvellos instead of the Recruiter since the Torm faction hit is so much bigger but I'm not sure I can last much longer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uchianaxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ChianaXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/02 9:00:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure about the big hits from larger CoV mobs, but it took less than 2 weeks to max Zek faction just killing trash in Skyshrine, and that was with moderate playing time (no marathons).<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiceisfun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IceIsFun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/02 9:02:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> Are you a rogue or other class that can use Sneak? If so, that's a great way to get the heads in.<br><br>If not, I'd suggest AE-killing massive amounts of dwarves and dwarven-wolves. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ustixum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stixum</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/02 9:16:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> After ~120 dorf heads and ~24 kobold paws I am ally to rif, zek and scowls to Tormax.  This is after 5 days of mind numbing green con dorf killing.  Haven't figured out why I decided to switch from ally to dorf &amp; CoV to giant yet, but I will never switch again after this... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaanmage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aanmage</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/02 9:36:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> The best way to raise Tormax faction is killing Yelinak or Dain and if your guild did Yelinak once, they can do it again. Killing Icewell dwarves is also good for Zek/Riff. As far as switching goes, it is a common misbelief that Kael quest armor is far greater across the board than SkyShrine quest armor. I added it all up and came up with the following totals for a full suit of each:<br><br>-----Kael -------------- Skyshrine<br>AC = 199 -------------- 176<br>STR = 40 -------------- 49<br>STA = 22 -------------- 21<br>DEX = 34 -------------- 37<br>AGI = 33 -------------- 47<br>SvM = 14 -------------- 27<br>SvF = 2 --------------- 5<br>SvC = 4 --------------- 13<br>HPs = 185 ------------- 235<br><br>I realize that an extra adjusted 34 AC is nice, but are the complete sets really so different? I am still trying to figure out a compelling reason to not stay on CoV/Dain faction until NToV killing fooks it up. If someone can show me the piece of Kael/Tormax gear that is so proundly superior to comparable SkyShrine/Yelinak gear, maybe I will be a believer. Haven't found it yet, but always willing to learn new things.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Aaldekk</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udubbo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dubbo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/02 10:01:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> I agree, but... they seem to want faction to turn in Yel's head, not so they can quest Kael armor. =P<br><br>I have Deceiver's because my guild is a giant-aligned guild. One major selling point most people seem to miss when comparing the two? Well, I dunno about other servers, but on my server the VAST majorty of HoT/West Wing capable guilds are on CoV faction. NToV capable guilds don't typically bother sitting in west wing farming armor. Getting armor has been a lot less complicated with multiple guilds trying to share HoT, while we've had west wing to ourselves.<br><br>Back on topic, I think the easiest way to raise faction is killing the Dain. Clearing the other royal dorfs = nice faction, not just the dain. Only downside is Dain kills can possibly be few and far between (not sure of your situation), so faction might come sooner in the long run by grinding it out. Skyshrine is probably the best place for that. Easiest kills for solid faction hits. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvisceragalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Viscera Galen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/02 10:25:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> With the quest nerf (can't turn in quest items while invis), does this affect sneak also? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulenardo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lenardo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/02 10:38:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> no if you are invis you are invis,, sneak is not invis.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/02 3:04:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> Go kill dragons in West Wastes.  I went from Max KoS to Kromzek (thanks AoW hits <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) to dubious in 6 hours killing most of the nest dragons a few times each, its much faster faction than killing in Skyshrine (but SS can be done solo when needed).   Once you get Kromzek to dubious turn in all those heads and paws to Bvellos and you should be ally to Zek after 27 heads, and ally to Tormax before you turn them all in.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usheanearrowless.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheane Arrowless</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/02 4:28:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> You say here that sneak works on bvellos, ok, but how can you prevent the other giants from attacking you ? I am viewing this from the KoS perspective, if i have misunderstood you, plz tell me, if not, im very interested in knowing how to get to him with sneak.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwemic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wemic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/8/02 6:15:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> The other giants in the bank are on Zek faction as well. There is a wanderer though who sometimes paths near the bank that is on a different faction.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaanmage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aanmage</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/9/02 7:45:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> Good point on armor farming in ToV, typically the west wing isn't camped all that much. My armor comparison table was a general musing over the types of quest armor, nothing more. <br><br>Aaldekk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unaekkil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Naekkil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/9/02 9:29:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> 2 things.<br><br>1) have you turned in heads to the Kromriff Recruit for Riff/zek faction hits? these seem to be higher from my pas experience and make iit easier to turn in at the bank later.<br><br>2)Patch message said you can not innitiate a trade while invis, ie start a trade. Can you still start a trade and then get an invis? haven't tried yet to find out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucelalrondecatur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celalron Decatur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/9/02 3:15:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> I went to the Recruiter last night to see if I could turn in a few heads just to get my faction to non-KoS so as to be able to get to Bvellos. Unfortunately, the Recruiter is still scowling to me so when I gave him a test head, he simply ate it. I even took a faction hit back when I killed him to see if he had the head on him but nothing.<br><br>Didn't try the initiate-trade-first-then-invis suggestion so not sure if that would work. May try it tonight though.<br><br>And I'm a Warrior so can't use Sneak. Damn Rogues <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utpfethos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TPFethos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/9/02 5:11:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> took me a good 3 months pure factioning, ZERO exp to go from max ally coldain and dain, to max all zek and tmax <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uewanakanach0king.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ewan aka nach0king</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/10/02 6:57:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> Other than the wanderer that paths near the bank, I was never aggroed sneaking behind Bvellos while KOS, by the others in the bank. Then again I was re-hiding between handins. If you just have Sneak it could be risky but you can gate/feign/run as required. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usirigudernesskat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siri Gudernesskat</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/10/02 3:27:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> I wasn't bottomed on my Rif/Zek, but it took me about 1.5 weeks of killing Coldain Wolfmasters in GD.  I used sneak to turn in heads to the Kromrif Recruiter until I was dubious to Rif and Zek, then I used sneak to turn them into Captain Bvellos until I was indifferent.<br><br>As for comparing Kael to SS armor...I'd go with SS BP, Kael arms and legs, and skip just about everything else - there's better stuff to be had that isn't hard to get (Barbed Dragonscale Boots, CC Gauntlets, SC Wristbands;  Circlet of Suffering is harder to get but IMHO far superior to Deceiver's/Shadow Crowns).  Of course, doing the above requires switching factions at some point.  Without switching factions...either one is cool, whatever HP you lose with SS arms and legs you'll get back with the BP, and you'll end up with more AC with Kael, more resists with SS.<br><br>And keep a Mrylo BP on you for healing (6 sec. cast time vs. 14.5).  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucelalrondecatur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celalron Decatur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/10/02 11:47:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> I got my GoDS today so I thought I'd come back and share some final info on this.<br><br>I had a Shaman guildmate of mine help me with the invis-after-trade-window trick mentioned a few posts above and it worked flawlessly. About 20 Coldain heads got me dubious to Riff and another 20 got me dubious to Zek. I then went to Captn Bvellos in the bank area and turned in about 65 more Coldain heads and 120 ice kobold paws to him. This got me ally to both Riff and Zek and amiable to Torm. Unfortuantely, Tormax (who had popped just moments before) still wouldn't give me the quest text so I knew I needed more. I grabbed 2 more heads from GD and 32 more paws from friends and turned those into Bvellos for another 10 faction hits, which was just enough to put me over.<br><br>Again, I was not max-KoS to Torm when I started but I think I was fairly close to it. In total, the faction work included:<br><br>- 2 Yelinak hits<br>- 1 Dain hit<br>- 107 Coldain heads<br>- 152 Ice kobold paws<br>- 4 days killing dwarves and wolves in GD<br>- 4 hours killing mobs in SS<br>- Maybe 1 hour on a few raid mobs in WW<br><br>Anyway, maybe some of this will help others down the road as well. I'm just glad it's over. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubondarelli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bondarelli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/11/02 2:38:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious faction woes</span><hr size=1> Dwarf eads are actually some awesome faction hits, if you have 100 of them you should have no problem hitting nonkos/ally using sneak.<br><br>The best way to build zek faction (not sure if there are tormax hits here) without  doing hand ins is by killing in ss. Also, an easy way to turn in heads while kos to zeks is have a monk pull the Captain to the outside of the bank and FD it, and you can go ahead and turn heads/paws into him while kos. The heads are very nice faction hits.<br><br>If you're kos to the riff, the recruiter (can't remember offhand?) just inside Kael from the EW zone is a great way to build riff faction. Just hide sneak your way behind him and turn in a few heads at a time until you are non kos with riffs.  I wouldn't waste any more heads than the minimum it takes to be nonkos with the riffs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=4888.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=4888.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4888.topic&index=18><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=4888.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=4888.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4888.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4888.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border